INSERT INTO `phpbb_posts` VALUES (4,4,0,2,8,'10.8.200.26',1310947865,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','About Ask GSAA [UG] ...','Hi !\n\nWelcome to [b:406hekva]Ask GSAA [UG][/b:406hekva] <!-- s:) --><img src=\"{SMILIES_PATH}/icon/smile.gif\" alt=\":)\" title=\"Smile\" /><!-- s:) -->\n\n[b:406hekva][size=120:406hekva][color=#BF0000:406hekva]What is Ask GSAA [UG] ?[/color:406hekva][/size:406hekva][/b:406hekva]\n[j:406hekva][b:406hekva]Ask GSAA [UG][/b:406hekva] basically, is a fast query resolution system for IITB students. It enables students to directly reach the [b:406hekva]GSSA [UG][/b:406hekva] : General Secretary of Academic Affairs in case of academic issues; also enabling the academic council to improve the present academic scenario in IITB by serving as a complete record of academic problems faced by students.[/j:406hekva]\n[b:406hekva][size=120:406hekva][color=#BF0000:406hekva]How does it work ?[/color:406hekva][/size:406hekva][/b:406hekva]\n[j:406hekva]IITB students can login to [b:406hekva]Ask GSAA [UG][/b:406hekva] using their LDAP credentials, even outside campus. Once they login to this system, they will automatically be presented with the forum corresponding to their branch. All the other forums &#40;corresponding to other branches&#41; remain hidden from standard users, to avoid unnecessary clutter.\nAnyone who has access to the particular forums can answer the queries, and is most welcome. GSAA [UG] of course has access to all forums.[/j:406hekva]\n[b:406hekva][size=120:406hekva][color=#BF0000:406hekva]Freshmen Forum  Ask GSAA [UG]  Moodle[/color:406hekva][/size:406hekva][/b:406hekva]\n[j:406hekva][b:406hekva]Freshmen forum[/b:406hekva] was started by SMP &#40;Student Mentor Program&#41; to address the queries of curios freshmen. It was not necessarily academics related and more importantly, it was not about the problems they face &quot;inside&quot; IITB. And [b:406hekva]Moodle[/b:406hekva] is a virtual learning environment, not for general non-course-specific query resolution.\nAsk GSAA [UG] is an entirely different system, which will be a complete log of problems faced by students and hence would enable us to make the system better.[/j:406hekva]\n[b:406hekva][size=120:406hekva][color=#BF0000:406hekva]What to &quot;Ask GSAA [UG]&quot; ?[/color:406hekva][/size:406hekva][/b:406hekva]\n[j:406hekva]Any issue which you find with the academic system, not very literally though <!-- s:P --><img src=\"{SMILIES_PATH}/icon/razz.gif\" alt=\":P\" title=\"Razz\" /><!-- s:P -->[/j:406hekva]\n\nHope you would make the full use of this, and help us improve the academic system <!-- s:) --><img src=\"{SMILIES_PATH}/icon/smile.gif\" alt=\":)\" title=\"Smile\" /><!-- s:) -->','7b268e0a671aa91061e574d9555c1bc1',0,'RgQ=','406hekva',1,1311067040,'[UG]',2,4,0),(5,5,32,64,0,'10.3.133.46',1310986217,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','People who couldn\'t register for HS core courses','There are quite a lot people who could not register for the HS core courses due to various reasons. They haven\'t been alloted any course amongst the four listed. What should be done ?','52cba4244fc7e65e7f46eaea258e4ae6',0,'','1gwazrqy',1,0,'',0,0,0),(6,6,32,80,0,'10.2.2.35',1310991904,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','False Backlog','Hey,\n\nASC says I have a backlog in HS 443. Hence I am unable to register. It\'s been a year since this problem initiated and hasn\'t been solved till now. Please look into it.\n\nAishwary Dale\n5th Year DD Student\nChemical Engineering','fdefbc4f044c3f9f235217fa8aeef1a3',0,'','1foxhqqa',1,0,'',0,0,0),(7,7,32,93,0,'10.209.4.2',1310994188,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Allotted Minor with unfulfilled pre-requisites !','I have been allotted the CS 419 minor in my 3rd semester. After the allottment i came to know that the course had some pre requisites. I had no such info about the same when i filled it in the preference list. Infact i was told that all CS courses on list are without a pre requisite. I could easily have got a minor in the electrical dept.(as people with lower CPI have got it). What am i supposed to do now..\n\nActually i know a lot of people who are facing the same problem..','b5a11210444601c6c74ae1ac1184a51f',0,'','23v004bc',1,1310994687,'Changed thread title',2,1,0),(8,5,32,73,0,'10.5.71.49',1310994337,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: People who couldn\'t register for HS core courses','same query, even i couldn\'t register for it.\nKindly tell what should be done, shall we do the course registration or wait?','12194b425c9abd7c504b0aae2d4bbbdd',0,'','sg83xwu1',1,0,'',0,0,0),(9,7,32,2,0,'10.8.200.25',1310994636,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: CS 419 Minors','Yup .. quite a lot of my friends have similar issues.\nSome have been allotted SI 402, which has SI 417 as a pre-requisite.\n\nPlease clarify what they should do now ?\n\n[color=#BF0000:5s4xparl][b:5s4xparl]PS[/b:5s4xparl] : I am changing the thread name to make it more general ...[/color:5s4xparl]','2586f9dfa6f5b104a9787a0be6cc552c',0,'Qg==','5s4xparl',1,0,'',0,0,0),(10,8,32,107,0,'10.6.100.99',1310996505,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Taking an institute elective','I wish to complete one institute elecctive this semester but its worth 8 credits while the curriculum allows for only 6 credit worth of institute elective. Can i take the course? If yes, how will I be graded?','3fac76e5dae5b93df81da578a80b853e',0,'','3v80hijf',1,0,'',0,0,0),(11,9,30,114,0,'10.209.4.2',1310997197,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','MM 304 backlog &amp; others','Hey ramanjit, \n\nthe registration page is showing mm 304 as backlog. it showed the same error last sem as well.\nAlso, it is showing mm 657 - design and application of engineering materials as core course whereas the curriculum is mm 654 - advanced composites as core course and one department elective. when u click mm 657, it shows that the course is not running this semester.\nto sum, many issues and registration is not getting done. please look into it. \nregards, \nHarsh','2b00d7e6030d9b3ec2386ffdb67348c3',0,'','15e3vxq3',1,0,'',0,0,0),(12,10,11,110,9,'10.209.4.1',1310997245,1,0,1,1,1,0,'','CS-4th year','can sm1 plzz concisely lay down the details relevant for me . Am tired of receiving/reading so many mails on gpo and cse','e05cf09e14b2a3d9feca1a7dccfea7a0',0,'','nfhhbclo',1,0,'',0,0,0),(13,5,32,61,0,'10.4.172.86',1310997281,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: People who couldn\'t register for HS core courses','All those who could not get any HSS Core Course can register for HS 301/303/305/307 in the \n[b:386lrs2e]Additional Courses /Extra Courses [/b:386lrs2e] slot given as the last line on the Registration interface. \nStudents are advised to do this tomorrow as we will incorporate a suitable TAG (HSS Core which is not there right now) for the above said courses \nby tomorrow i.e 19th July 2011. \n\nThanks \nRamanjit','f0abff846b52d4ab8e40b3fff7cbe420',0,'QA==','386lrs2e',1,0,'',0,0,0),(14,7,32,115,0,'10.209.4.2',1310997339,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Allotted Minor with unfulfilled pre-requisites !','Even check for EE 210 also please','6cd32a518bc49d5985fef013d5afd287',0,'','3452hew3',1,0,'',0,0,0),(15,6,32,61,0,'10.4.172.86',1310997577,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: False Backlog','We are looking into it and a list has been forwarded to the academic office. It will be done by tomorrow.','aa4cc8363d7b88fc42e67ebd834b7218',0,'','1h4uxax6',1,0,'',0,0,0),(16,10,11,61,0,'10.4.172.86',1310997711,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: CS-4th year','Post it on the Computer Science Btech queries forum.','1c131991a2897eac5417f533b98e8e10',0,'','2ljkyv14',1,0,'',0,0,0),(17,11,11,2,10,'10.8.200.25',1310997804,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Problem with course registration [ASC]','It seems there is some problem with ASC\'s course registration interface for 3rd sem courses.\n\nWhen I verify my courses, I get an error regarding [b:sp2j1tcf]CS 207[/b:sp2j1tcf] :\n\n[b:sp2j1tcf]Course :[/b:sp2j1tcf] CS 207\n[b:sp2j1tcf]Registration rule Exception :[/b:sp2j1tcf] There is no entry for this course in the current semester.\n[b:sp2j1tcf]Approving Authority :[/b:sp2j1tcf] 1. Head Of Department, 2. Faculty Advisor.\n[b:sp2j1tcf]Reference :[/b:sp2j1tcf] Reference to Academics Rule Book\n[b:sp2j1tcf]Can Override :[/b:sp2j1tcf] No.','d5eda500a5ea8e47876968f3bddbb4e7',0,'QA==','sp2j1tcf',1,0,'',0,0,0),(18,10,11,2,0,'10.8.200.25',1310997906,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: CS-4th year','[b:2sc18nrn][color=#BF0000:2sc18nrn]Thread moved to CSE BTech sub-forum.[/color:2sc18nrn][/b:2sc18nrn]','b2435b81e55b645dcfba0dbb5576c962',0,'Qg==','2sc18nrn',1,0,'',0,0,0),(19,8,32,61,0,'10.4.172.86',1310997958,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Taking an institute elective','You can take it as you need to complete 12 credits as Institute Elective, so take an 8 credit and a 4 credit course. You will be grade as any other course','e363547c4db75bd3ef88e61595bcda61',0,'','f5e87q9h',1,0,'',0,0,0),(20,12,15,117,0,'10.2.42.5',1310998471,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','course registration for UG 2nd year','hi\n\ni have a doubt regarding the courses for 2nd year this sem.the department websites shows the following courses in this semester- MM 201,203,204;EE 101;IC 211.\nhere is the link-\n<!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.met.iitb.ac.in/main.html?smenu=academics/section&amp;content=academics/curriculum/curriculumBtech2\">http://www.met.iitb.ac.in/main.html?sme ... ulumBtech2</a><!-- m -->\n\nhowever, the course registration page in asc shows the course MM212 instead of IC 211 for registration, which is actually a course which we have in the 2nd sem according to the dept. website.\n\nthis problem is only for the B.tech students. the DD students are getting IC 211 on their course registration page and not MM 212.\n\nCan you please confirm this, whether the B.tech students have IC 211 or MM 212 this semester???\n\nthanks..!!\n\nRugved Likhite','0fec39aee4276e417f4d6c036ae33fde',0,'','3bahdp47',1,0,'',0,0,0),(21,13,15,119,0,'10.2.112.37',1310998747,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Lab course for 2nd year students','Its given that lab course for us is IC211 is in the 1st sem and MM212 in 2nd on dept website....whereas its asking us to register for MM212 this sem and not IC 211 on the asc website. Also dual degree students are having IC 211. Can you please sort this out at your earliest? Thanks.','6af72107a9929719c6ee1491e2ae3a5d',0,'','3tmw9jpg',1,0,'',0,0,0),(22,14,33,121,0,'10.4.161.19',1310999587,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','5th year Elec DD Communication registration','This query is relevant for all elec DD Comm 5thies. Our curriculum on EE website says we are supposed to take one department elective this semester, but the interface on ASC is expecting us to register for 2 dept electives. Will you please get this issue resolved?','4fb8d63eed7beb01cf58aac1857ba800',0,'','3t0u189v',1,0,'',0,0,0),(23,8,32,107,0,'10.6.100.99',1311000157,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Taking an institute elective','But i have already done one institute elective(worth 6 credits) in my 2nd year. Doing a 8 credit course now( in my 3rd year) will total it to 14 credits...How will I be graded then?\n[quote=&quot;anand.ramanjit&quot;:1o9uu81u]You can take it as you need to complete 12 credits as Institute Elective, so take an 8 credit and a 4 credit course. You will be grade as any other course[/quote:1o9uu81u]','d49d8a0be54300968ceff34ed8135f31',0,'gA==','1o9uu81u',1,0,'',0,0,0),(24,15,8,71,0,'10.5.130.39',1311001993,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Credit Limit','according to the institute rule book, there is a 42 credit per semester limit (except for catagory 1) but the core courses for us (2nd year aero) have already reached 42 credits and there is no room to take the pre-registered minor courses (or any other course) for us...','ea77b44ee84044846d8becc2bbca97d2',0,'','2f38dshy',1,0,'',0,0,0),(25,16,14,133,0,'10.5.162.12',1311003735,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','BTP','how to register for BTP in mechanical department ??','bd6342aefb4dc2e51057321a67ba55ab',0,'','1qu92deg',1,0,'',0,0,0),(26,17,32,150,0,'10.209.4.2',1311008634,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Institute Elective Slot','Does the Institute Elective course to be chosen have to be in a particular slot? My department\'s timetable (<!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.ee.iitb.ac.in/~eeoffice/timetable/Allacademic-load2011_12/timetableautumn2011_12.pdf\">http://www.ee.iitb.ac.in/~eeoffice/time ... 011_12.pdf</a><!-- m -->) seems to suggest that the UG Institute Elective is only meant to be run in slot 3. Or can we go ahead and chose any course from any other department (as long as it doesn\'t clash with other courses, of course)?','3f11c21cc02d549f29f14ac0c0b2eb25',0,'','1nquh2gc',1,0,'',0,0,0),(27,8,32,61,0,'10.4.162.86',1311009307,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Taking an institute elective','You will be graded on 14 credits only.. This would require Dean\'s permission as the core cpi has some pre-defined components, Institute electives being one. All the students in core performance have 12 credits of them. So for 14 I would suggest that you meet Dean AP once. You can do that before 1st August 2011 till course adjustment is allowed','6bb85786686ee0ffb799f9093ecd9447',0,'','386t77ds',1,0,'',0,0,0),(28,17,32,61,0,'10.4.162.86',1311009426,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Institute Elective Slot','You can go ahead and chose [b:2bn747xl]any course from any other department (as long as it doesn\'t clash with other courses[/b:2bn747xl], of course ) . Institute Elective is just given as an indicator in the department time table.','5e12855cd95fc99040a0a71b14ef738a',0,'QA==','2bn747xl',1,0,'',0,0,0),(29,7,32,163,0,'10.209.4.2',1311011252,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Allotted Minor with unfulfilled pre-requisites !','Even i got that CS419 course and now by this post i have come to know that i am not eligible for that course.So what should we do now?','8bf79b6612f74bc10a70e2b759c85209',0,'','1mjjwfws',1,0,'',0,0,0),(30,8,32,161,0,'10.209.4.2',1311011396,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Taking an institute elective','I have a similar query:\nDoes the Institute allow more than 2 courses as an Institute elective? Even after completing 12 credits can one opt for more Institute electives?','e92dca87b602ac8b2a5e6f52fca74ba2',0,'','250lyubd',1,0,'',0,0,0),(31,17,32,161,0,'10.209.4.2',1311011584,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Institute Elective Slot','Can Institute electives taken run in minor slot given I don\'t wish to take a minor?','03173c6a9ebfc8cd4276acbb1fd9f1b9',0,'','1351kvzw',1,0,'',0,0,0),(32,8,32,107,0,'10.6.100.99',1311011702,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Taking an institute elective','Thanks\n[quote=&quot;anand.ramanjit&quot;:2dafpgqj]You will be graded on 14 credits only.. This would require Dean\'s permission as the core cpi has some pre-defined components, Institute electives being one. All the students in core performance have 12 credits of them. So for 14 I would suggest that you meet Dean AP once. You can do that before 1st August 2011 till course adjustment is allowed[/quote:2dafpgqj]','7fbfdca1786b476bcaa58bfcac4a6ce3',0,'gA==','2dafpgqj',1,0,'',0,0,0),(33,18,15,164,0,'10.209.4.2',1311012017,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Late Registration','HI Ramanjit,\n\nI am doing an internship in UBC, Vancouver and I\'ll be reaching the institute on 27th night. The change of schedule wasn\'t possible as it would have cost me a lot. So there will be a problem in registration. The talks between ICs and Dean concluded that the people reaching late should register late with fine. But the last date of registration is 25th. Should I at least register myself earlier? Please tell me what to do.\n\nSahil Dhingra\n09011024','4e26c7f7a7b05852537d063a0f8d9f75',0,'','eqjqn5kg',1,0,'',0,0,0),(34,7,32,61,0,'10.4.162.86',1311012351,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Allotted Minor with unfulfilled pre-requisites !','You can take other courses as minors as well. But this would strictly be only with the course instructors\' permission. There are two options in front of you right now \n1) The course you want to take as minor has been fully exhausted with the allocation---in that case your CPI can be matched with the cut-off for that course and instructor can permit you to take that course \n2) The course you want has not been fully exhausted ---in that case you can get the seat or the instructor\'s permission directly and on a first come first serve basis. \n\nGo to the ASC registration interface and under the Additional/Extra Courses register for that course once you have convinced the instructor and then an ovveridable error will come which can be processed by the Academic office after you have submitted the print out of that form with the instructor\'s ( of the other course ) signature approving your request to take the other course as minor.','98db554720b8ab958b86cecc89fd9133',0,'','37c7dd1a',1,0,'',0,0,0),(35,8,32,61,0,'10.4.162.86',1311012468,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Taking an institute elective','@ Voraniket : You can not take more than 12 credits as insti electives without Dean AP\'s permission','2209a0af48478fb4d6be649e63a848aa',0,'','gig3edcs',1,0,'',0,0,0),(36,17,32,61,0,'10.4.162.86',1311012534,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Institute Elective Slot','Yes','93cba07454f06a4a960172bbd6e2a435',0,'','322ivdto',1,0,'',0,0,0),(37,15,8,61,0,'10.4.162.86',1311014426,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Credit Limit','You can take minor if your faculty adviser and Dean AP permits you to overload. It would be better if all the willing students make a common appeal to the Facad and forward it as a single application to the Dean AP office.','202e25279b876a0aca91ec70545f5a4a',0,'','9t0o7sd8',1,0,'',0,0,0),(38,19,32,173,0,'10.209.4.2',1311014443,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Compulsory Attendance in courses not registered in 1st week','If a student is not registered for a course till even the end of the first week (due to obvious reasons: slot clash, not sure about the courses in case of electives, etc) how will that be tackled to comply with the compulsory attendance rule?','355a89dbdd24da6608fe70e91deed0c2',0,'','3lxks73t',1,0,'',0,0,0),(39,7,32,176,0,'10.209.4.2',1311014544,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Allotted Minor with unfulfilled pre-requisites !','with in how many days after registration should this be done ? i mean going to prof and getting the sign, submitting it in acad office.','e5f9322bb6ec7d176a075a96900fb9c8',0,'','1cp4byz