,'','Re: BTP to fulfill Honours requirement','it is an additional course','c84e4a28413bf255afe112764dd851fe',0,'','9cmo3u01',1,0,'',0,0,0),(179,63,12,139,0,'10.5.101.39',1311538233,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Selecting an institute elective','\'you cannot take an institute elective of your own branch without HODs permission.','a66d2e501129a2d5697fb2d3931a4cde',0,'','19t8knjd',1,0,'',0,0,0),(180,64,14,139,0,'10.5.101.39',1311538483,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: changing HSS core','Take the permission of the course instructor (of Reading literature). Write an application to acad office signed by the course instructor.','5ff5d6129d7a83df64b62126e9eb8f24',0,'','1grmghnu',1,0,'',0,0,0),(181,5,32,139,0,'10.5.101.39',1311538636,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: People who couldn\'t register for HS core courses','what is the error message?\n\noverride it and get the approval of the approving authority.','ca48fa2305be7a8ab10595799e269463',0,'','1l4hw9yh',1,0,'',0,0,0),(182,60,32,139,0,'10.5.101.39',1311539232,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Re-Tagging of courses','Tagging interface will open in the last semester of a students stay at IITB (i.e. 7th and 8th sem for Btechs and 9th and 10th sem for Duals). At that time you can tag any minor/honor course as insti elective/department elective. You can also tag any additional learning courses as insti or department elective. However, you are not allowed to tag a insti elective elective to minor without the permission of the 2 HODs and Dean AP. \n\nYes in the final transcript the tag associated with the course will also be mentioned.','155d9ed8dbfdb8b0a30131774494b2d2',0,'','jz1uwwr2',1,0,'',0,0,0),(183,65,32,145,0,'10.10.2.3',1311614683,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','CS207 minor course','The limit to the number of students registered for CS207 minor exceeded. There were 40 students before and the course instructor had permitted 3 more and all of them are being shown in red now. Why is that and what would happen now? Will these students have to go back to the previous minor they had taken?','bae1125579eab5947ab7f854150a7480',0,'','2uagdevb',1,0,'',0,0,0),(184,66,11,319,0,'10.6.161.121',1311616929,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Regarding Department Electives','We have to take 3 department electives each semester of fourth year, so what if I do 7 courses as department electives. Will I be given an option to remove 1 of these electives for my final CPI ?','caf200458f5655e1d7dc744617119614',0,'','3b64b8fk',1,0,'',0,0,0),(185,66,11,139,0,'10.5.101.39',1311618262,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Regarding Department Electives','you can\'t do all 7 courses as department elective. You have to do 6 courses as department elective and 1 course as additional learning. The additional learning one will not be included in your B.tech CPI. You will have the choice of which course you want as additional learning and which as department elective through tagging.','520d29f2cac5f73966677976d85d8070',0,'','xcloannr',1,0,'',0,0,0),(186,65,32,139,0,'10.5.101.39',1311618700,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: CS207 minor course','these students have to take approval from course instructor. They registered according to the overriding rule exception. To know more about the registration rule exception, read the blog: <!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://riitb2011.blogspot.com/2011/07/registration-rule-exceptions-overriding.html\">http://riitb2011.blogspot.com/2011/07/r ... iding.html</a><!-- m -->','90aca3f88a093742fed139a6ee4a8426',0,'','qyd6y3yw',1,0,'',0,0,0),(187,67,32,320,0,'10.7.40.77',1311626194,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','CS 419 Audit','I wish to take CS 419 as an audit. (It is running as a minor course this sem in slot 5)\nWhen i try to register for it online, the asc interface gives me the message that this course has no listing in the time table. \n\nPlease look into the issue.','318ba7a8ada667f4a601caade6cff345',0,'','25mcucdb',1,0,'',0,0,0),(188,65,32,145,0,'10.10.2.3',1311646299,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: CS207 minor course','They had taken the course instructor\'s signature too. What would happen then?','32fc67d9ed737226f9e8399d86f28bb6',0,'','2mr8f4va',1,0,'',0,0,0),(189,68,30,321,0,'10.2.202.84',1311663573,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Cant register for core course','hey\nMM 407 is a core course for all 4th year students but its still not showing in Core Course bulletin. for the time being i have registered for that course as dept elective.\nkindly make note of that and resolve issue asap.','043067e68c2c45899110738bb2798763',0,'','9glenvpf',1,0,'',0,0,0),(190,66,11,319,0,'10.6.171.221',1311664830,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Regarding Department Electives','Thanks for the info , also can I tag the courses as honors which I take as department electives now.','e8e3b3b68950a20cbfa973bb788d4f88',0,'','aapxtm0o',1,0,'',0,0,0),(191,69,11,322,0,'10.6.161.18',1311666756,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','IDC minor/insti elective','I want to do IDC course Animation and Technology as insti elective. I have heard around from a lot of people that IDC course can be done only as minor. I had pre-registered for it as minor also. So two option: do it as insti elective or do it as minor and tag it as insti elective later. Any of this is feasible?','b6342f7d0c502350b0bbb56e39be3372',0,'','34rtr7f5',1,0,'',0,0,0),(192,66,11,139,0,'10.199.2.27',1311669691,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Regarding Department Electives','to tag any department elective as honors (and to take institute elective as minor) you need to take permission of HOD and Dean AP (for minor you need to take permission of HOD of minor department as well).\n\nyou can tag anything from honors/minors to dept/insti elective, but you need permission for doing the opposite.','05b99dae4de2a19c9bfda4afa72d130e',0,'','1bnmjm34',1,0,'',0,0,0),(193,69,11,139,0,'10.199.2.27',1311669833,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: IDC minor/insti elective','you can do it as a minor now, and tag as institute elective later.','f0fe2bdec9fa8c04184f4e7f515b0d12',0,'','26zzro6n',1,0,'',0,0,0),(194,65,32,139,0,'10.199.2.27',1311670246,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: CS207 minor course','They will be registered, once they submit the form in acad office and manual entry is done by the academic office.','ef47eacc7cd5112cd6016ce8f3c9d1c3',0,'','26b8wmtv',1,0,'',0,0,0),(195,70,32,323,0,'10.105.12.61',1311671912,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','TA allotment','When will the TAs for the first year courses be alloted. If they have been, can the allotment list be displayed here...?','b62fc31a679fba3b19dcf4c0bf6a3806',0,'','2471z2k5',1,0,'',0,0,0),(196,70,32,139,0,'10.199.2.27',1311674099,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: TA allotment','Professors of the respective courses will contact their TAs as mentioned in the initial mail sent.','0eb270391addccf40a808fdac379b212',0,'','1z0q95hm',1,0,'',0,0,0),(197,71,30,328,0,'10.110.0.28',1311859076,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','change of specialization for dual degree students','can a student change his/her specialization after completion of 4 semesters ?','091265162d935f143957dae391a3ecb9',0,'','2trl63w5',1,0,'',0,0,0),(198,71,30,61,0,'10.4.162.25',1312024928,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: change of specialization for dual degree students','Yes the student can do that with the concerned department\'s DUGC ( Department Undergraduate Committee\'s ) recommendation. So please discuss this issue with your facad and then get it discussed in DUGC which can recommend and Dean will approve to be processed by the academic office. It takes around one month to complete the procedure in case no objections are raised by any stakeholder.','1ea52460ed9fa8695ce8ee0ae5f57859',0,'','1jnmhq8c',1,0,'',0,0,0),(199,72,32,316,0,'10.6.162.36',1312310860,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Problem accessing courses in Moodle','Hi there,\n\nI have dropped HS-303 Psychology course and have taken HS-305 Read Literature as HSS Elective.\nHS -305 is shown in my &quot;Registered Courses&quot; on ASC.\nBut, I am not yet being able to access the HS-305 Moodle Page. It says : \n\n&quot;This course is not enrollable at the moment. This is done inorder to prevent outsider\'s access to the course.\n\nPlease note that ASC does the auto-enrolment only for the courses which you have registered through ASC.\n\nIf you want any additional courses(just to access the study materials), kindly contact the concerned faculty of this course. A faculty has the full control on the Moodle course and can add additional Teachers/TAs/Students which is discussed in detail here at Moodle Help Pages (internal link may not work outside IITB Campus).&quot;\n\nPlease tell me whom should I contact to get this fixed.\n\nRegards,\n\nSaurav Aryan','1c560cf142d9169af2137b409352a372',0,'','2x2gfndy',1,0,'',0,0,0),(200,72,32,61,0,'10.199.2.27',1312970248,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Problem accessing courses in Moodle','Send a mail to <!-- e --><a href=\"mailto:asc.help@iitb.ac.in\">asc.help@iitb.ac.in</a><!-- e --> for moodle problems','4cbc40417929e13f9919df1ae4c7a5a8',0,'','1kjphyto',1,0,'',0,0,0),(201,73,33,337,0,'10.7.45.75',1312983901,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Retagging inerface for third year students','Will a retagging interface be opened for third year students this year? If yes, when?','477fa36d45094b7186f3672b66aa33b1',0,'','2yvxbepc',1,0,'',0,0,0),(202,74,33,96,5,'10.7.1.69',1312987713,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Course Tagging Queries','The course Tagging interface has opened. I have a few queries. It says that the course can have the following tags:\n1. C : Core Course \n2. D : Departmental Elective \n3. E : Honours Elective \n4. G : Masters Elective \n5. H : Humanities Elective \n6. I : Institute Elective \n7. M : Minor Course \n8. O : Honors Course \n9. P : Masters Core \n10. T : Additional Learning\n\nQueries:\n1. Can you tell us the difference between D,E,G? Do DD students have courses with E or G tag?\n2. Also, I believe DD students do not have any courses with the following tag: E,G,O,P. Correct me if I am wrong.\n3. Also, it would be great if you can provide us with the number wise breakup of each courses, so we can make sure that we have done enough courses of each type or change the course tag accordingly.','71ec2eed3362d387dd471db5469f6e1a',0,'','23r8x27c',1,0,'',0,0,0),(203,73,33,61,0,'10.4.162.25',1312996323,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Retagging inerface for third year students','Retagging interface will be opened for you when you will be eligible for placements i.e next year if you are a B Tech or two years from now if you are a DD.','d28e990be2f36af7300387bc04ef71d2',0,'','22reg207',1,0,'',0,0,0),(204,74,33,61,0,'10.4.162.25',1312997033,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Course Tagging Queries','1) D is a department elective\nE is honors elective ( in some dept.s the honors requirements are divided into 2 parts : One in which students have to do some specific course codes which are fixed; these are tagged O and the other wherein students can do a certain number of department electives to fulfill the 30 credit criterion for completion of Honors; these are tagged E )\nG is Masters Elective : For Dual Degrees a total of 96 credits are to be completed which includes 72 credits of DDP and 24 credits of Master\'s coursework. Under these 24 credits some dept.s have fixed some specific courses to be completed and these are tagged as P and some courses have been kept floating to be taken as some dept. electives with codes starting from 6 or 7 ( PG electives) and these are tagged as G \n\n2) Answered above\n\n3) Answered above. But each dept has its own sweet way to divide the curriculum into various components. Better check <!-- m --><a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.ee.iitb.ac.in/~eeoffice/curriculum-2008/ELECTRICAL_DD_COMM.htm\">http://www.ee.iitb.ac.in/~eeoffice/curr ... D_COMM.htm</a><!-- m -->','b391af3d272466cf64aa67d5c302a530',0,'','3f0t9vcb',1,0,'',0,0,0),(205,74,33,61,0,'10.4.162.25',1312997152,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Course Tagging Queries','@ Saswat please shift this to the general queries section','f489d90dab894398022cc6e91953440d',0,'','2kdact3s',1,0,'',0,0,0),(206,50,14,193,0,'10.4.72.44',1313029029,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: IEOR as insti Elective','The tagging interface doesn\'t permit us to take IEOR as insti elective. Kindly look into this.','5d78b413d4277d54400f494aef00aa1e',0,'','352ktqsf',1,0,'',0,0,0),(207,50,14,61,0,'10.4.162.25',1313053321,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: IEOR as insti Elective','The tagging interface permits additional learning and minor tags to be changed to Institute elective tag. If you have tagged an IEOR course as something other than these then re-tagging to institute elective option will not show up on the interface. However you can manually do that by writing an application addressed to Dean AP endorsed by your FACAD and HoD stating the reasons for the change of tag. These are exceptions which cant be generalized and the interface cant accommodate these. For this very reason are we giving you an alternative manual route. Hope it clears the air.','2ca86ac2b052832425708a289aa743e7',0,'','1p6taqho',1,0,'',0,0,0),(208,75,9,340,0,'10.8.114.46',1313070559,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','tagging interface','can we revise i.e, modify the changes made on the tagging interface if done before 16th ?','3764a3e7d179efaebf62d3c06e72500a',0,'','m9p13rhv',1,0,'',0,0,0),(209,76,9,340,0,'10.8.114.46',1313073570,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Additional courses','If i tag one of my minor course as institute elective, then my minors would come as additional courses on my final transcript, right??\n\nSo, does my CPI on the transcript include these additional courses, or in general how will the CPI on the transcript be calculated?','80a8dd8257965a6c2fb2cd6e2c8ccb3a',0,'','3f62nizy',1,0,'',0,0,0),(210,77,9,311,0,'10.7.86.32',1313074699,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Tagging for SLP to include it for hons requirement','What should I tag my SLP-1 to include it into my honours requirement?\n\nOptions--\n\n- E (Hon. Elective)\n- O (Hon. Course)','583e467a0b01be6b851733af812ddd5c',0,'','29ctwpo7',1,0,'',0,0,0),(211,75,9,61,0,'10.199.9.222',1313144274,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: tagging interface','You need to take the print out of the duly signed form and submit it in the Dean AP office. \nIf you want to modify tagging submit another form printout repeating the same procedure and \nask for cancellation of the first form before 17th Aug','367cd53d5f64e6cf529f4d9633c8f19d',0,'','ljgd46c1',1,0,'',0,0,0),(212,76,9,61,0,'10.199.9.222',1313144434,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Additional courses','on transcript you would receive these CPIs\n1) Core \n2) Minor ( if 30 credits completed ) \n3) Honors ( if completed) \n4) Additional courses (neither minor nor honors if any ) \n5) Overall (  taking all the courses creditted by you in IIT B)','43148dd0c556a1c6aca303ae3da7b6bb',0,'','38h6vdjy',1,0,'',0,0,0),(213,77,9,61,0,'10.199.9.222',1313144469,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Tagging for SLP to include it for hons requirement','E','3a3ea00cfc35332cedf6e5e9a32e94da',0,'','3efepuu5',1,0,'',0,0,0),(214,78,11,344,0,'10.7.10.58',1313297669,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Number of Institute elective','If my total number of institute electives is more then two, will the extra one\'s be counted in the CPI or only two will be included in CPI and other will be displayed as additional courses during placement time ?','850b58c119f0313e966425fd3885c5b2',0,'','3f3xmbqj',1,0,'',0,0,0),(215,79,32,345,0,'10.7.10.58',1313302267,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Tagging a course with FR','I took a course as Institute elective, but I got FR in that. Now I want to change its tag to minor but the course is not displayed in the change tag page in asc. How can I change its tag ? Will this course be reflected in my CPI during placements ?','9c401f5c9dacc7045b2a9aab9ab1851c',0,'','1xwn2jfp',1,0,'',0,0,0),(216,80,33,346,0,'10.209.4.1',1313309323,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Tagging, Backlogs, and Mistags','Do clarify the following points -\n\n1.What happens if I pick a departmental elective and convert it to an additional learning course?\n   I am supposed to have completed eight electives so far, but by doing so I\'ve completed only 7.\n   Does this count as a backlog? If so, does it appear on transcripts - the ones for placements / the\n   ones I\'ll get for apps in November?\n\n2. An extra course I\'ve completed is currently tagged I (although it was just a normal extra course). \n   I intend to get this changed to a D. Procedure?','75dd59326c9ad11a3a205bbc6ba27b97',0,'','36273lx1',1,0,'',0,0,0),(217,81,13,347,0,'10.2.130.67',1313340475,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Electives','What is exact meaning of [b:21w08g98]Department/Open[/b:21w08g98] Elective and [b:21w08g98]Institute/Department[/b:21w08g98] Elective?\nIs there any difference between these two?','6d2b3ecab968e53f16506332227ec9d9',0,'QA==','21w08g98',1,0,'',0,0,0),(218,78,11,139,0,'10.5.101.39',1313446357,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Number of Institute elective','only 2 will be included in CPI','5317802159a28032a969169c5967f207',0,'','28w9ntbh',1,0,'',0,0,0),(219,80,33,139,0,'10.5.101.39',1313446592,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Tagging, Backlogs, and Mistags','1. Yes that will count for a backlog. It will appear on transcript too\n\n2. Tag I implies Institute Elective and D implies Department elective. You cannot do a course of any other department (which is tagged as I in your case) as department elective.','de60b753fe5e57bb03d20c8883d2651a',0,'','3klsu01z',1,0,'',0,0,0),(220,79,32,139,0,'10.5.101.39',1313447022,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: Tagging a course with FR','You cannot tag a course which you have not cleared.','391b92761fd6fe4ff60067e9cbff6a79',0,'','13pae7zm',1,0,'',0,0,0),(221,82,32,348,9,'10.3.212.17',1313915847,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','MCM Scholarship','I am a second year student and received the MCM scholarship last year. Do I need to apply for MCM again this year to avail the scholarship?','9eb619c4addc797b23c5741c8c7ff327',0,'','34agr3qg',1,0,'',0,0,0),(222,82,32,348,0,'10.3.212.17',1314257461,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Re: MCM Scholarship','Please reply.','b301e44f505fd6b118534a88dafe9743',0,'','2wr81iy3',1,0,'',0,0,0),(223,83,32,88,0,'10.127.250.94',1324625800,1,0,1,1,1,1,'','Mathematics and statistics minor','Hi, \n   Minor courses of maths and stats are not there in the minor list. Aren\'t maths courses going to be listed in minor allotment?','04e14ddc20a2b959523fd0b1be3f14a0