INSERT INTO `reviews` VALUES (13,'EE',731,'Taguchi Methods','Prof. Apte','ishan.shrivastava','The course was basically aimed at using statistical methods to obtain best settings of parameters for optimum results. The course was taught using applications in fabrication and manufacturing.','2 Quizzes, 1 Mid-Sem, 1 End-Sem, 1 Assignment before every exam','no value','Easy','2012-06-08'),(14,'AE',0,'','','nidhi_shanbhag','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-08'),(15,'EN',632,'Waste to Energy','Anuradda Ganesh','neeraj.kuldeep','Biomass Gasification and gasifier design,\r\nBio gas, Bio Diesel,  ','2 quizz, Assignment depend upon mood(4-5 max), midsem and endsem questions were predecided.','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(16,'PH',103,'Electricity and Magnetism','C.V.Tomy','110260026','I learnt the basic concepts regarding them which were very essential. But the number of formulae that was stuffed in this course makes it impractical to remember beyond a semester.','The course was maybe a little on the voluminous side. No. of quizzes and assignments was apt.','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-10'),(17,'AE',0,'','','sksiitb','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(18,'EN',410,'Energy Management','Santanu Bandopadhya','ashish.mendhekar','Pitch-concept in heat exchangers , Basic electrical concepts and some plant utility concepts . ','Load was appropriate as 2 quizzes and a project .','no value','Difficult','2012-06-10'),(19,'CH',426,'Rate Processes','Prof A.Q Contractor and Prof Anindya Dat','aakanksha_dimri','Physical chemistry above and very different from the JEE level.\r\nToo much derivations to remember by End-Sem.','2 quizzes, 10 Assignments.\r\nMidsem and Endsem follow the trend of the instructor.','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-10'),(20,'EP',424,'','','sayali.bhosekar','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(21,'CH',423,'Organic Chemistry III','KPK','aakanksha_dimri','Tons of Reagents and Conditions, not even able to remember all by endsem.\r\nVery useful course for people planning to study Synthesis in future.','3 quizzes, 7-8 Assignments, Midsem, Endsem.\r\nCourse needs consistent study and performance throughout the year.','no value','Difficult','2012-06-10'),(22,'AE',617,'Plates and Shells','Prof. Tarun Kant','vishal_khatri','1. (Approximate) Theory of elastic deformation of plates assuming linear, isotropic, homogeneous material: As with everything else, this is really a 3D problem. But we assume that the plate is thin (thickness << length or breadth) and approximate it to a 2D problem.\r\n\r\n2. Ditto with shells. Note that the shell problem is still a 3D problem (after \'thin\' assumption) in linear (X-Y, cartesian) coordinates. So, we need to use polar coordinates to model it as a 3D problem assuming thickness (radial direction) to be small\r\n\r\n3. The most important learning from this course, perhaps, was the broad outlook towards Solid Mechanics- what are general assumptions to be taken while beginning a theory from scratch, what contradictions are okay to have, what contradictions need to be solved, what approximations are okay to have, etc.','Pretty heavy! You will have 1-2 hours of extra lectures *every week* in addition to the 3 slotted lectures a week. There are assignments (roughly 1 in a week) which are easy and directly related to lectures. Prof. Kant did not take quizzes but most other instructors would, if they teach the course. All the study materials were available on CDEEP which was an added convenience.','no value','Difficult','2012-06-10'),(23,'AE',0,'','','ravindra.m','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(24,'AE',0,'','','sk.savant','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(25,'AE',0,'','','sk.savant','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(26,'EN',640,'Solar Photovoltaic, Fundamentals, Technologies and','Saibal Sarkar','prakhar.khandelwal','Since I am EE student, pre-midsem portion was the same I studied in my core course. Its about p-n junction diodes. Post-midsem portion was basically on design of solar-cell, optimisation of efficiency of solar cell, organic solar cells. Post midsem portion was boring and one needed to cram the stuff. Course wasn\'t interesting and if one wants to do this as an elective, one needs to have interest in solar cell and willing to take on similar courses in future. Alone this course won\'t serve any purpose. ','1 Assignment, any number of quizzes(surprise as well as announce quizzes), midsem, endsem. \r\nWeightage : quiz -35\r\nMidsem 15\r\nEndsem 35\r\nAssignment 15','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(27,'AE',0,'','','abhinav.rastogi','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(28,'CL',152,'Introduction to Chemical Engineering','Prof. Vinjamur Madhu','vibhorej','The course title can be misleading since the course does not offer you an overview to Chemical Engineering which should be the motive of any DIC. Instead the course offers the basics tools, namely Mass Balances and Energy Balances, with which every  Chemical Engineer should be equipped.\r\n\r\nAccording to me, it is a very good as in a peace course and it does help you learn a lot.  One of the best parts is that there is an industrial visit to RCF after which you are expected to apply the same stuff to the RCF Plant, that you have learnt.','There were weekly assignments which had 5 to 6 questions but they had to be done in a group which were formed by the instructor himself. They were not such a burden since one person of the group took the responsibility every week.','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(29,'GP',416,'Structural Geology and Stratigraphy','Soumyajit Mukharjee','prashanth.iitb','Basic Geology Concepts, How difficult is the work of Geologists, About Indian Geography( a little bit)','3 Quizzes, No Assignments(very rare)\r\n','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(30,'EE',722,'dgfdf','gdgsdgf','ypradeep','gddf','gdgdg','no value','Difficult','2012-06-10'),(31,'HS',472,'psychology of health','Mrinmoyi Kulkarni','kapil_yadav','health psychology aur kya...!!!\r\nunlike other courses, lectures were not very boring.... Prof tried 2 make them as interesting as possible.also, grading is lenient.\r\nIt surely enhanced my awareness of attitude towards health.','no quizzes, only 1 assignment and 1 presentation.\r\nmidsem was subjective but endsem was objective. The prof said that from next year she will conduct only objective paper.paper was easy.','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(32,'EE',602,'Radar Systems','K P Ray','akshatjain','Contents: Basic radar equation, radar signal processing (signal integration, pulse compression, matched filter, ambiguity function optimizing range and doppler resolutions), radar cross section fluctuation, radar elements(transmitter, receiver, duplexor), radar noise and clutter mitigation, types of radar (MST, tracking, jamming, surveillance, doppler etc), RFID, Radar design.\r\nExperience:  quite interesting, no pre-requisites for non EE students as well, a must do for EE-CSP','3 quizzes, 1 application assignment (to be coded), 1 project (study of existing radar), endsem','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(33,'AE',0,'','','akash23','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(34,'CS',207,'Discrete Structures','Prof. Krishna Shankara Narayanan','100070031','Modules : Graph Theory, Propositional Logic, Automata theory','3 Quizzes, 5 assignments. Excellently handled course. ','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-10'),(35,'EN',610,'Hydrogen Energy','Pratibha Sharma','saurabhvs','Basic concepts of hydrogen energy, manufacturing, storing and utilization','No assignment. It just has one course seminar which is not very challenging. Sometimes the course work become monotonous and boring. If you are good at remembering things then u can easily make to BB+.','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(36,'CE',310,'Transportation Systems Engineering','Gopal R. Patil','vaibhav_saboo','Given in course info .. but interesting learning and basic stuff (easy to understand especially if you were good in JEE Physics)  .. Join only if interested .. grading is bad!!!','Course load was high .\r\n5 surprise quizzes , 2 assignments, 1 seminar , 1 project , midsem and endsem..','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-10'),(37,'CE',201,'Solid Mechanics','Tarun Kant','saubhagya.s.rathore','Basic of small element analysis in terms of stresses and strains.','Moderate','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-10'),(38,'CE',222,'Structural Mechanics','Prof. M. Inamdar','ishita.shrivastava','Shear loads on beams, bending moments.\r\nBending moment diagrams, Shear force diagram. Solving for deflections due to these loads. Statically indeterminate structures.','Moderate','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-10'),(39,'CH',222,'Organic Chemistry II','Prof. Suvarn Kulkarni','ashuiitb','Organic Reactions, Mechanisms, Selectivity aspects','3 Quizes, No assignments','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(40,'CH',222,'Organic Chemistry 2','Prof.Suvarna Kulkarni','mayankboob','Carbonyl chemistry','The course load is light and some questions are directly dependent on slides so paying attention in class is most important.\r\nThe course is slow in first half and picks up pace in second as you start to get a feel of the subject.\r\nEnd sem is slightly on the harder side.','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(41,'EN',610,'Hydrogen Energy','Pratibha Sharma','hemantbansal','Expected - Very deep knowledge into hydrogen energy, manufacturing, storing and utilization\r\nBut I learnt only starting part of the course i.e. formation of hydrogen gas.','I had this course in even semester/2012. It was core course for Ph.Ds due to which this course had become too heavy. Everything was taught in full detail which made this course boring, dull and tiring. All these phds will get higher grades and UGs can expect only below  8 grade.','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-10'),(42,'EE',659,'The First Course in Optimization','Soman S.A.','sancharsharma','It was a basic overview of optimization. There were not many real life applications in the course, so it is very useful only if you want to do further courses in optimization.','The course load was apt. 3 assignments, 2 quizes and no mid sem, only end sem.','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-10'),(43,'PH',544,'General Theory of Relativity','P Ramadevi','sancharsharma','I learnt enough about all the relevant concepts  required to study Relativity further (the meaning and physical intuition about bending of space time, basic motion in gravity, gravitational waves, etc). However, if you are looking for a rigorous mathematical study of GTR, the course is not for you.','5-6 assignments, 2 quizzes.','no value','Difficult','2012-06-10'),(44,'AE',0,'','','nishantkhanduja','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-10'),(45,'MG',406,'Operations & Supply Chain Management','Prof. Rahul Patil','ashray','It was mostly applying formulae\r\n1. Optimizing time on an assembly line\r\n2. Queuing Theory \r\n3. Excel Solver\r\n4. Production plan ','Not very strenuous.  ','no value','Difficult','2012-06-11'),(46,'HS',219,'Application of Psychology to Modern Life','Pooja Purang','ashray','80% course is same as a Hs301 Psychology course. ','No quizzes. Just a file/report to be submitted for 25 marks which includes a Viva. Midsem -30 & Endsem -45','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(47,'AE',617,'Plates and Shells','Prof. Tarun Kant','vishal_khatri','1. (Approximate) Theory of elastic deformation of plates assuming linear, isotropic, homogeneous material: As with everything else, this is really a 3D problem. But we assume that the plate is thin (thickness << length or breadth) and approximate it to a 2D problem. 2. Ditto with shells. Note that the shell problem is still a 3D problem (after \'thin\' assumption) in linear (X-Y, cartesian) coordinates. So, we need to use polar coordinates to model it as a 3D problem assuming thickness (radial direction) to be small 3. The most important learning from this course, perhaps, was the broad outlook towards Solid Mechanics- what are general assumptions to be taken while beginning a theory from scratch, what contradictions are okay to have, what contradictions need to be solved, what approximations are okay to have, etc. ','Pretty heavy! You will have 1-2 hours of extra lectures *every week* in addition to the 3 slotted lectures a week. There are assignments (roughly 1 in a week) which are easy and directly related to lectures. Prof. Kant did not take quizzes but most other instructors would, if they teach the course. All the study materials were available on CDEEP which was an added convenience.\r\n','no value','Difficult','2012-06-11'),(48,'MM',407,'Iron and Steelmaking','N B Ballal','deepoo','General heat and mass balance in Ironmaking and Steelmaking\r\nIronmaking: Old processes like Blast furnace and their details. Some newer process of extractions like COREX, MIDREX\r\nSteelmaking: Purification of Iron. Process involved are BOF, LD - converter etc.\r\nIt is about what you do with molten steel. \r\nOthers: Continuous casting.\r\n\r\n','3-4 assignments, 2 quizzes. 12+ tutorials','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-11'),(49,'AE',0,'','','dinnuisgreat','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(50,'AE',600,'Introduction to Biomedical Engineering','Prof. S. Mukherjee , Prof. S. Sen','nuruddin.bahar','Heart , Kidney , ECGs , MRIs , Biosensors , Cell Mechanics','Quizzes : 5-6   \r\nAssignments : 10','no value','Difficult','2012-06-11'),(51,'CS',218,'Design and Analysis of Algorithms','Prof. Ajit Diwan','karthik.c.s','How to understand the algorithmic structure of a problem. ','Well balanced. 3 quizzes, best 2 taken into consideration.','no value','Difficult','2012-06-11'),(52,'BM',658,'Biomedical Microsystems','Rohit Srivastava','harsh.maheshwari','Basics of Lithography, Designing of Microelectrical Mechanical Systems (MEMS), Nano Electrical Mechanical Systems with a view towards Biomedical Applications. (Basically a lot of elec +meta + a little of Bio)\r\n\r\nExcellent course if you actually want to start of with the basics of Lithography and MEMS Designing.\r\n\r\nHelps Meta Students in Courses like Semiconductors. Course is updated and covers all the recent developments. ','Course Load was peaceful. Short Quizzes (about 5) of small weight-age covering trivial syllabus from the lecture slides.\r\n\r\nMid Sems and End Sems have the same questions as those in the quizzes along with the addition of a designing problem.\r\n\r\nAt the end of the course you can apply the concepts very well.','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(53,'AE',0,'','','jigar.sura','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(54,'CS',101,'computer science and programming','Soumen Chakrabarty','akshay.saxena_iitb','Language: c++\r\nContents: Basics, functions, arrays, *BOOST Libarary, recursion, dynamic programming, map, unsorted map, binary tree, linked list and many more','There were two written quizes, one lab quiz,  endsem, and a AP contest(to distinguish between AA and AP), No Project, One evaluated lab per week.\r\n','no value','Difficult','2012-06-11'),(55,'EE',708,'Information Theory & Coding','Prof. Sibi Raj Pillai','vivek.agrawal','The course is good in the beginning. Talks about a lot of information theory like source coding, channel coding, Huffman codes, etc. In the second half, it becomes more coding oriented with error correcting codes, gaussian channels and the like. Its very good learning but one needs to attend the lectures or the course will get out of hand! The prof teaches well. Please buy the textbook.','2 quizzes + 2 paper reviews + 5 assignments. Assignments were very well designed and quizzes were easy.','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-11'),(56,'EE',708,'Information Theory and Coding','Sibi Raj B Pillai','deekshasinha','It started with the basics of information theory and then moved on to more involved topics related to channel transmission and analysis of error .. ','The course was pretty simple to begin with but after the midsems the load shoot up! The content became quite difficult . Also the assignments included paper reviews which wasnt that straightforward. \r\nI would not recommend this course to be taken by 3rd year students . ','no value','Difficult','2012-06-11'),(57,'EE',706,'Communication Networks','Saravanan Vijayakumaran ','sudipto_mondal','Introduction to computer communication networks and layered architecture. \r\n- Protocols for wired and wireless communication systems: ALOHA, CSMA/CD, Performance modelling and analysis.\r\n- Internetworking issues: Bridges, Routers and Switched networks. Routing and Flow Control algorithms in data networks.\r\n- Local Area Networks: Ethernet and FDDI. Design and analysis.\r\n- Point to Point Protocols and links: ARQ retransmission strategies\r\n- Point to Point Protocols and links: ARQ retransmission strategies.','4 Quizzes of 5% weightage each (20% -Quizzes)\r\n4 Assignment including 1 Network simulation coding (20%-Assignments)\r\nMidsem-30%\r\nEndsem-30%\r\nAssignments were comparatively more difficult than the exams, hence solving them was always a good exercise.','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(58,'EN',615,'Utilisation of Solar Thermal Energy','J.K. Nayak','09d17008','1. How to do design calculations of almost all solar systems\r\n2. How to do the thermal performance analysis of all solar thermal systems\r\n3. Exposure to all types of solar thermal systems','Quizzes : 2 planned each of 20 marks, around 6-7 surprise quizzes of 10 marks; these quizzes comprehensively covered the portion, \r\nEndsem 50 marks.\r\n','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-11'),(59,'CL',152,'introduction to chemical engineering','Prof. Vinjamur Madhu','110020065','mass and energy balances are the most important concepts which i have learnt after the end of this course. A visit to RCF gave me a practical experience of these concepts.......','there were four homeworks having 8 to 10 questions. we were given one week to do this. and there were four quizs also having four to 5 objective questions..','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(60,'AE',0,'','','jainik.shah','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(61,'EE',654,'Power Electronics 2','Prof. Vivek Agarwal','rahulpramod','Linear DC regulators, their pro\'s and con\'s. \r\nThe basic approach used in the original papers concerning the evolution of voltage and Current DC-DC convertors. 5 Major topologies in isolated power supply scheme and practical implementation. Fundamental approach for Transformer design in the above topologies. Inductor design from scratch. \r\nSmall signal models and analysis of DC-DC convertors, Control schemes used in switching. Some standard S-domain compensation schemes. ','4 assignments, 3 of them were graded (total -15%). Each assignment around 3-5 questions, each had 1 or 2 simulations. Mid Sem 25 %. Course project 20% (Implementing closed loop convertors- we had to build a forward convertor from scratch with closed loop control). End sem 40% types.\r\nAssignments were adequate and decent. \r\nThe course project gave good learning about developing high power circuits, which we normally don\'t in WEL labs. \r\nExams were a bit lengthy but were decently difficult. To wrap up, must do for Power enthu UG\'s. Apt continuation for EE-222; A very do-able and interesting course. ','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-11'),(62,'AE',713,'Space Flight Dynamics','Prof. Ashok Joshi','113010002','The course is divided into two parts viz.  Ascent Mission Modelling & Attitude Dynamics (Pre Mid-Sem); & Orbital Mechanics & Re-entry mission (Post Mid-Sem). There are no prerequisites for the course.','Marks distribution: \r\n1. Four assignments (3 marks each); \r\n2. Four Quizzes (5 marks each); \r\n3. Mid-Sem (20 Marks); \r\n4. Class Participation (10 Marks); \r\n5. Assignment Presentation (8 marks)  \r\n6. End-Sem (30 Marks)','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-11'),(63,'CL',152,'Introduction to Chemical Engineering','Prof. Vinjamur Madhu','110020039','The course includes mass and energy balances which are really interesting and easy to learn.You will get to know something more about Raoult\'s and Henry\'s law.Infi peace course if silly calculation mistakes avoided.','4 weekly assignments were to be done during the entire sem for which enough time was given.4 quizzes also took place which covered all the topics in a proper manner.And these were all very easy.','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(64,'HS',624,'Contemporary Issues in Philosophy of Mind','Prof.Rajkishore Nath','rojasthomas','I felt  that the method of teaching of the professor is not good at all.\r\nThe classes were extreamly boring.\r\nThe grading system is not good.\r\nthe evaluation system is also not good.\r\nI am totally disappointed after taking this course.\r\nI havent get anything from the prof and from the classes.','There is not much load.\r\nsimply go to the class and sleep.\r\nno quizzes and no assignments\r\nonly mid sem end sem and a seminar\r\n\r\nIT DOESNT MEAN THAT YOU CAN EASILY GET THE GRADE','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-11'),(65,'AE',152,'','','sarangminhas','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(66,'HS',456,'Introduction To Creativity and Creative Writing','Neelima Talwar','abhishekraj','Importance of Creativity and how to apply it to everything I do. Also, my dream is to become a published writer and this course greatly helped me find the appropriate form and structure for my creative writing. ','One quiz worth 20 marks + optional creative assignments. I would recommend doing the optional assignments as she takes it into account for giving the final grades and the prof is very nice so you will also get to learn more if you do her assignments.','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(67,'ME',203,'Fluid mechanics','B.C puranik','malviyaprateek91','Basic Concepts of Fluid mechanics','2 quiz\r\n5 to 8 Assignment','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-11'),(68,'CL',356,'Process Plant Utilities','Ganeshan','jatinjakharia','questions in exam are different from what he teaches in the class.\r\nmostly he sets the same paper every year','zero load, attendance marks, no assignments, no quizzes, class participation marks.','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(69,'PH',544,'Elementary Particle Physics','Prof. Kumar Rao','prashant_iitb','Quark Model, Basics of Quantum Electrodynamics, Feynman Diagrams,Electorweak Unification, Spontaneous Symmetry Breaking','No quiz, 4 assignments, Mid sem, End sem','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-11'),(70,'PH',420,'Astrophysics','Prof. Narshimah (TIFR)','prashant_iitb','Stellar Interiors,Star Formations,  Galaxy Evolution, Cosmological Principle, Expansion of Universe','No quiz, 4 assignments, Mid sem , End sem','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(71,'PH',304,'Statistical Physics','Prof. Dibyendu Das','prashant_iitb','Micro Canonical, Canonical, Grand Canonical Ensemble, Quantum Gases, Fermi Dirac Statistics, Bose Einstein Statistics, Bose Einstein Condensate.  ','No assignments, 1 Quiz, Mid Sem, End Sem','no value','Difficult','2012-06-11'),(72,'EE',357,'Compound Semiconductor Materials and Devices','Prof. B.M. Arora, Prof. Subhananda Chakr','akshayagarwal','The pre-midsem part, taken by Prof. B.M. Arora, is a general introduction to III-V semiconductors (GaAs, InAs etc.), their bandgaps, doping. and heterojunctions. The lectures are easy-paced and can get a little boring sometimes. The recommended book (Pallab Bhattacharya) is quite hard to find, and is required for supplementary reading.\r\n\r\nThe post midsem lectures, taken by Prof. Chakrabarti, are almost exclusively focused on the professor\'s own research area. He covers Molecular Beam Epitaxy, Quantum dots, Rapid Thermal Annealing and Infrared Photodetectors. The lectures are a little more open-ended as some unsolved research questions are discussed (and sometimes given as assignment!)','Prof. Arora gives one assignment per week, and is quite flexible with submission dates. He did not take any quizzes, but his midsem was quite difficult. \r\nThe course gets really heavy after the midsem, as Prof. Chakrabarti gives lots of assignments, ranging from analysis of quantum dot data on OriginPro to surveying papers on dots. He takes a quiz in addition to the endsem, and they are both lengthy. ','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-11'),(73,'HS',303,'Introduction to Psychology','Meenakshi Gupta, A. Khan','10d170004','It\'s a very interesting subject, especially if taught the right way.','No load at all. Reading from the book is more interesting and is often easier than reading from A. Khan\'s slides.','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(74,'EE',677,'Foundation of VLSI CAD','Prof. Sachin Patkar','09004029','Learnt different algorithms for circuit optimization such as McCluskey\'s algo, Branch and Bound algo. Got introduced to basics of dynamic programming, FSM optimization, finding stuck at faults in circuits. Was introduced to Bluespec Verilog. A very informative course. As Patkar sir puts it - Basic course for EECS.','Not much.\r\n1 coding assignment + 1 term paper + tutorials + midsem + endsem','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(75,'HS',307,'Sociology','Prof. Rowena Robinson + Prof. Ramesh Bai','09004029','Basics of Sociology - What is sociology? How is it different from Psychology and Economics? Different interpretations of Sociology (Marx, Weber and Durkheim). The idea of the social. Eight sutras of Sociology. Different features of a society. Idea of criticality and common sense in sociology. Indian sociology - Caste System in India. Super interesting course. Excellent Profs','2 quizzes + midsem +endsem\r\nExtremely peaceful!','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(76,'AE',0,'','','vinaykrishnan','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(77,'CS',348,'Computer Networks','Prof. Aniruddha Sahoo','09004029','Basics of Internet. There were 5 chapters in the course - each corresponding to one of the layers: Application layer, Transport layer (TCP/UDP), Network layer (IP), Data link layer and Physical layer. Very informative course.','3 programming assignments + 3 short quizzes + midsem +endsem \r\nThe course load was on the higher side. The assignments were very useful.','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-11'),(78,'ES',204,'Enviromental Chemistry','Sanjeev Chaudhary','vishal_saugat','Enviroment problems and solutions to them','Chill - 1 Midsem(30) , 1 ppt(15) , 1 Endsem(50)  + attendance(5) ','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(79,'ID',406,'Basics of Animation','Sumanth Rao','manishreddy','Basics of animation, using 3D softwares like maya, 3ds max and video editing softwares like vegas and after effects.','We had to submit 4 assignments during the whole course. No quizzes as such.','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(80,'ME',480,'Two Phase Flow and Heat Transfer','Prof. Arun Kumar Sridharan','raunakbardia','There are loads of charts and graphs to study thorughout the course which is a little tedious but also are generally used in industries. ','Assignments based on each topic, 4 quizzes ','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-11'),(81,'AE',0,'','','devashish','','','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(82,'ME',617,'Rapid Product Development','K P Karunakaran','gauravbharti','Something about different about of machining and product development. ','7-8 Quizzes + Impositions (1 imposition if you get less than 75% marks, 2 imposition if you get less than 50% marks and 3 impositions if you get less than 25 % marks).\r\nThe questions in the quizzes are arbit and requires cramming up lot of stuffs and writing an impositions requires atleast 1-2 hrs. So the course load is little too much without much of learning.  \r\n\r\nContent and grading is chill but so many quizzes and writing impositions is a headache. ','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(83,'ME',754,'Textile Machine Design and Automation','A Guha','gauravbharti','About different types of machines used in textile machining and different type of such processes','Course load is chill. Open notes+books examination. Questions asked are mostly from class notes and materials given. \r\n\r\nGrading is also peace. \r\n\r\nQuizzes-1\r\nProject/seminar- 1 \r\nmidsem-1\r\nendsem-1','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(84,'ME',445,'Fuels and Combustions','Arindrajeet Choudhary','gauravbharti','Fuels are not covered much. It covers mostly combustion and various properties associated with it. ','Quizzes-3\r\nAssignment-2\r\nmidsem-1\r\nendsem-1\r\n\r\nCourse load was not that difficult and content was easy too. So studying regularly and going to the class will automatically fetch you good grades. ','no value','Moderately Difficult','2012-06-11'),(85,'ME',617,'Rapid Product Development','Prof. K P Karunakaran','zamanrao','It was about rapid prototyping, virtual reality, CNC and Computer graphics','Infi Quizes ( nearly every alternate week) each with its 4-6 pages of imposition.\r\nSo don\'t take it for easy grading/easy course content because this will cause you less time to study other subjects and the same effort if you put in any other course, you can get dassi while here after so much effort you will land up in 8 or 9','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(86,'ME',476,'Managerial Principles and Practices','S.D.Jog','swapnilchichani','Well, nothing related to the course name. It was general knowledge and discussion based. It is important you go to the class and participate in the discussions. One course where there is no alpha beta gama delta or any sort of differentiation or integration. \r\n\r\nIts like you come up with a topic and discuss it in class- the topic can range from Recession to reservation to faculty in IIT. \r\n\r\nThe course instructor is one of the best I have seen in IIT. Totally different from any other faculty member and one person to whom you can reach out and bitch about this system openly. \r\n\r\nThe bad grades of previous years in course statistics are so just because average attendance in class was 4/5. All those who attend the class get a 9 or a 10. Its pretty chilled out. \r\n\r\nAnd yes, the end sem and the mid sem papers are corrected by the students themselves.','NONE. \r\nEven the mid sem and the end sem were chilled. Had to prepare not more than 10 minutes for mid sem and end sem. ','no value','Easy','2012-06-11'),(87,'MG',402,'Human Resource Management','Prof Ashish Pandey and Prof Bhargava Yad','rahulpramod','Organizations- basics, structure, culture, design ; Stakeholders, managers and their role; Ethics; Recruitment is covered in very good detail; Performance appraisal methods, need, effectiveness; Strategy management; HR Planning- effective work force utilization; ','Excellent course- entertaining lectures- very good profs- Peaceful grading; Must do for good knowledge and time pass..:)  ','no value','Easy','2012-06-11');
